"{\"uid\": \"christianpost.com-voices-olympics-closing-ceremony-should-convey-frances-apology.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Christian Post To enjoy our website, you will need to enableJavaScriptin your web browser.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 95, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Christian Post\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"our website\", \"from\": 28, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"your web browser\", \"from\": 77, \"to\": 93}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pleaseclick hereto learn how.\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pleaseclick hereto\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 114}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CP VOICES do not necessarily reflect the views of The Christian Post.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 177, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Christian Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"VOICES\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 136}, {\"ngram\": \"the views\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opinions expressed are solely those of the author(s).\", \"from\": 197, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Opinions\", \"from\": 197, \"to\": 205}, {\"ngram\": \"the author(s\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's contributions to intellectual studies in Western thought and culture have been noteworthy.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Western thought\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"intellectual studies\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 is an opportunity to show the world how much France has advanced from the 100 years prior when they hosted the Olympics in 1924.\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 352, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251405931325191e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 482}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that was an objective of the recent Olympics opening ceremony, France deserves a grade of \\\"F\\\" for its indecent portrayal of what the history of culture has treasured.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an objective\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"the recent Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 556}, {\"ngram\": \"a grade\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 581}, {\"ngram\": \"F\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"its indecent portrayal\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 615}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 646}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They depicted Leonardo Davinci's Last Supper in drag.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2436621565410677e-25, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0679572837018176e-30, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Christians and Church leaders were offended and rightly so, but I wasn't.\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999725574416747, \"rank\": 2.5445844973164908e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Church leaders\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Honestly, my reaction was one of pity for France and its organizers.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my reaction\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"pity\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 833}, {\"ngram\": \"its organizers\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was that their idea of encouraging a culture of inclusion?\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their idea\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lack of artistic discernment of a treasured international and cross-cultural painting reveals how deep France's culture has sunk.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1031, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lack\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 932}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic discernment\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"a treasured international and cross-cultural painting\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's pitiful.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024's ceremony splashed opprobrium on Davinci's iconic piece of art by disparaging his traditional depiction that continues to inspire people of all cultures.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251405931325191e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"opprobrium\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1114}, {\"ngram\": \"Davinci's iconic piece\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"his traditional depiction\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"all cultures\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A depiction that has captured the emotions of art lovers, whether Christian or not.\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A depiction\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"the emotions\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"art lovers\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1295}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic ceremony's sketch before a watching world challenged the treasured historical value of the Last Supper and mocked the rich traditional heritage of billions.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic ceremony's sketch\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1352}, {\"ngram\": \"a watching world\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"the treasured historical value\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"the rich traditional heritage\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"billions\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It crossed the line of decency and civility.\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"decency\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"civility\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its lewdness was taken to an unprecedented level.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its lewdness\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"an unprecedented level\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the plan of the organizers was to promote inclusion, they could have surely opted for other artistic and entertaining sketches that encouraged conversations among different thinking people.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the plan\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"other artistic and entertaining sketches\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"conversations\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"different thinking people\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The international backlash from people of every generation, nation, societal status, and political position was fired at the French organizers.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The international backlash\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1819}, {\"ngram\": \"every generation\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"nation\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"societal status\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"political position\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A young journalist,commented astutely: \\\"The West has officially fallen.\\\"\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A young journalist\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"The West\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So how is it that the French failed so miserably?\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The artistic director and mastermind behind the flamboyant opening ceremonysaid\\\"religious subversion [had] never been his intention.\\\"\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The artistic director\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"mastermind\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"the flamboyant opening ceremonysaid\\\"religious subversion\", \"from\": 2092, \"to\": 2148}, {\"ngram\": \"his intention\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whatever the \\\"intention,\\\" it was not inspirational.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the \\\"intention\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather, it revealed how ideology can be a force that sacrifices tradition, culture, historical contributions, and civility in order to force an agenda.\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ideology\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"a force\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2283}, {\"ngram\": \"tradition\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2309}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2318}, {\"ngram\": \"historical contributions\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"civility\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"an agenda\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Globally, commentators were sharp in highlighting how such blasphemous sketches always single out the Christian faith.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"commentators\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"such blasphemous sketches\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French organizers have apologized, but it's difficult to believe that such cultured people who are enriched with theological and philosophical heritages failed to anticipate the international condemnations.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such cultured people\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"theological and philosophical heritages\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2663}, {\"ngram\": \"the international condemnations\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How could such an educated and culturally rich nation not foresee such a debacle?\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such an educated and culturally rich nation\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2771}, {\"ngram\": \"such a debacle\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Consequently, the ceremony's mocking of Christian faith engendered global divisiveness.\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2841, \"end\": 2850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony's mocking\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"global divisiveness\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Note that this was not a sketch prepared for a private audience, though that would have also been questionable by cultured people.\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sketch\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 2920}, {\"ngram\": \"a private audience\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2952}, {\"ngram\": \"cultured people\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was planned with forethought that the whole world would be watching.\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"forethought\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3053}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole world\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did they care that billions of Christians would be offended by their choice of art?\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3125, \"end\": 3135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999725574416747, \"rank\": 2.5445844973164908e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"billions\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3121}, {\"ngram\": \"their choice\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3169}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did they care that an iconic painting that is treasured by history would be unfairly critiqued and denigrated?\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an iconic painting\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3215}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3244}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How could this have escaped their preparation processes?\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their preparation processes\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an obvious mocking of Christian values.\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3376, \"end\": 3392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999998995008, \"rank\": 1.0064477482585607e-10, \"text\": \"Christian values\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an obvious mocking\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where it backfired is that the French probably thought that their artistic display would resonate with inclusiveness.\", \"from\": 3394, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their artistic display\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3476}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusiveness\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, it caused a backlash and revealed how French culture is progressing inbias.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3567, \"end\": 3581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the contrary\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3527}, {\"ngram\": \"a backlash\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3549}, {\"ngram\": \"inbias\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But France has an opportunity to make its apology real.\", \"from\": 3605, \"to\": 3660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3609, \"end\": 3615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 3620, \"to\": 3634}, {\"ngram\": \"its apology\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has enough time to prepare for the closing ceremony where it can show the world some respect for how the past 100 years have brought diverse cross-cultural appreciation worldwide and growing civil discourse.\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough time\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3679}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3734, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"some respect\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3756}, {\"ngram\": \"the past 100 years\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3783}, {\"ngram\": \"diverse cross-cultural appreciation\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3832}, {\"ngram\": \"growing civil discourse\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a Christian, I acknowledge that not everyone believes like me.\", \"from\": 3873, \"to\": 3938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3878, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"not everyone\", \"from\": 3908, \"to\": 3920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So this is not simply another writing from a Christian who is whining about how his faith was caricatured.\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 4045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3984, \"end\": 3993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another writing\", \"from\": 3961, \"to\": 3976}, {\"ngram\": \"his faith\", \"from\": 4019, \"to\": 4028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ideologies can be messaged but they must also tolerate counter-perspectives.\", \"from\": 4047, \"to\": 4123, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ideologies\", \"from\": 4047, \"to\": 4057}, {\"ngram\": \"counter\", \"from\": 4102, \"to\": 4109}, {\"ngram\": \"perspectives\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is a hallmark of French contribution to Western thought.\", \"from\": 4124, \"to\": 4185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4146, \"end\": 4152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4169, \"end\": 4184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Western thought\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a hallmark\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the famous Frenchman Voltaire once quipped, \\\"I disapprove of what you say, but I will defend to death your right to say it.\\\"\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4313, \"entities\": [],